Open-Jellycore — https://github.com/OpenJelly/Open-Jellycore (GPL-3.0)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A Swift compiler-frontend for Apple Shortcuts.

`data/jellycore_facts.json` is projected from Open-Jellycore's catalogue
by `scripts/extract_jellycore.py`. Per action it carries: identifier,
Apple display name, parameter key names, OS-min. Plus Apple-namespace
control-flow structural identifiers from Compiler.swift.

Modifications:
- 2026-05-08: subset projection to JSON.
- 2026-05-08: dropped the upstream `enums` section (unused here).
- 2026-05-08: filtered out `jelly.*`-prefixed identifiers.

shortcuts-js — https://github.com/joshfarrant/shortcuts-js (MIT)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A TypeScript library for building shortcuts (~iOS 12). Informed this
project's per-action factory pattern, the output-UUID-per-action
convention, and the variable type taxonomy (`Ask`, `Clipboard`,
`CurrentDate`, `ExtensionInput`, `Variable`). Not vendored.

iOS-Shortcuts-Reference — https://github.com/sebj/iOS-Shortcuts-Reference
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A reference data repository (archived 2022; licence not declared). Source
of top-level metadata enums — `WFWorkflowImportQuestions`,
`WFWorkflowInputContentItemClasses`, `WFWorkflowTypes`, the icon-colour
palette, `shortcuts://` URL schemes. Not vendored.

`docs/sources.md` lists smaller community write-ups consulted in
addition.
